cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.ST

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new mathematical model for anomaly detection. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as anomaly detection is a common application of AI. Additionally, since the paper deals with security and detecting anomalies in data, it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
